- title   = 'Content: Content Modules';
- id      = 'content-modules';
- nav[id] = title;

+section( title, id )
	p This custom post type is provided via <a href="#webman-amplifier"><strong>WebMan Amplifier</strong></a> plugin.

	p Content Modules can be used as a reusable content injection to various website areas. They can be styled as <strong>icon boxes</strong>, so they are perfect for your services, features or benefits presentation.

	p For each Content Module you can set up a title, description text, custom link URL, custom link action, featured image and/or font icon.

	p If you use font icon, you can change the icon color and its background too. If you set both the icon and featured image, the <strong>special Content Module layout</strong> will be displayed: square featured image with overlayed icon on left and the module's content on right.

	p It is also possible to conveniently group Content Modules using dedicated tags.

	+tip( 'Display with <a href="#beaver-builder">Beaver Builder</a>' )
		p Use <em>"<strong>WM Content Module</strong>"</em> module in <a href="#beaver-builder">Beaver Builder</a> page builder.

	+tip( 'Modifications' )
		p You can modify the layout of this post type display with <a href="#css-classes">helper CSS classes</a>.

	+tip( 'Renaming the post type' )
		p If you would like to rename this post type, use the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/cpt-editor/"><strong>Custom Post Type Editor</strong></a> plugin. To rename the custom taxonomies related to this post type, use the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/rename-taxonomies/"><strong>Rename Taxonomies</strong></a> plugin.

	+tip( 'Custom posts order' )
		p For custom posts order you can use a plugin, such as <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/intuitive-custom-post-order/"><strong>Intuitive Custom Post Order</strong></a>.
